blog.title: The Video Game Art Archive
blog.description:
The Video Game Art Archive is dedicated to scanning and extracting classic video game artwork at the best resolutions possible!

Support us on Patreon!
We update four times a day with new artwork from long forgotten games that have never had their art available. Looking for a specific game? Check out the Archive! You might get lucky!
Also follow our other blog: Want to help us continue our work? Help via PayPAL

summary: Hey dudes, once again sorry for not being active on here (then again the whole Tumblr's new policy; which has nothing to do with...
body:
Hey dudes, once again sorry for not being active on here (then again the whole Tumblr’s new policy; which has nothing to do with me).

Remember when Super Smash Bros. had its little character animation cards from its website? I remember that there were about six animations that you can send to your friends. There were Mario,Donkey Kong,Yoshi,Pikachu,Link and Kirby. On YouTube someone had all but the Link animation. But luckily I remember what his animation was and his cartoony appearance. Geeze Link is always the unique one for me XD.

Art © Franchesca Huerta aka Chibi-Tediz/Chibi Brugarou

Link © Nintendo

Please do not use any of my characters or my work without my prior permission.If so, you will be warned
